# ROVEXO Image Safety — Canonical UI Rule (v1.0)

**STATUS: PERMANENT | MANDATORY | PLATFORM-WIDE**

The platform must **never** display broken image icons, browser default missing-image
glyphs, or `next/image` runtime errors from invalid sources.

## Single entry point

All UI imagery must render through **`SafeImage`** (`components/ui/SafeImage.tsx`)
or **`Avatar`** (`components/ui/Avatar.tsx` for user avatars).

❌ **Never** import `next/image` outside `SafeImage.tsx`.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — raw next/image with possibly empty/404 URL
import Image from "next/image";
<Image src={product.imageUrl} alt={product.title} fill />

// ✅ GOOD — validated source + runtime onError fallback
import { SafeImage } from "@/components/ui/SafeImage";
<SafeImage src={product.imageUrl} alt={product.title} fill />
```

## Validation before render

Use `isRenderableImageSrc()` from `@/lib/media/is-valid-image-src` when filtering
arrays (galleries, carousels) or mapping data before it reaches the UI.

Never pass `src=""`, `src={null}`, `src={undefined}`, or placeholder URLs to
`next/image`.

## Missing / broken images

| Case | Behaviour |
|------|-----------|
| Valid URL | Render normally via `SafeImage` → `next/image` |
| Missing / invalid URL | Official ROVEXO placeholder (`/placeholder-product.svg`) via plain `<img>` |
| Runtime load failure (404, expired) | Swap to placeholder via `onError` |
| Avatars | Use `Avatar` — initials fallback, `onError` hides broken photo |
| Decorative icons with known static paths | `SafeImage` with `fallback="hide"` |

The placeholder **must** use a plain `<img>` (not `next/image`) because the Next
optimizer rejects local SVG unless `dangerouslyAllowSVG` is enabled.

## Prohibited

- Browser broken-image icons anywhere on the platform
- `src=""` or dynamic src without validation
- Patching with CSS `display:none` on broken images instead of fixing the source
- New direct `next/image` imports in feature/page/component code

## Enforcement

- Vitest: `tests/image-safety-canonical.test.ts` scans the codebase for rogue
  `next/image` usage and asserts validation helpers.
- Listing Card freeze allows **broken image loading fixes only** — use `SafeImage`.
